edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.templates.subsystems

Class Feeder

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
      • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.templates.subsystems.Feeder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NamedSendable, Sendable

    public class Feeder
extends Subsystem

    One of the simplest possible subsystems that does anything. It consists of a single motor, this motor then controls opening and closing the motor through dead reckoning. It has three capabilities:

    • Open: Tells the motor to open the claw.
    • Close: Tells the motor to close the claw.
    • Do Nothing: Tells the motor to do nothing with the claw.

    Recommended next step: Wrist

    Author:
    Alex Henning

      • pushforward

        public void pushforward()
        Implements the Feeder capability. Simply tells the motor to move full speed in one direction, it is the commands responsibility to tell it when to stop opening. If the command doesn't, it will keep opening until the command ends and the default command ClawDoNothing takes over.

      • returnback

        public void returnback()
        Implements the claw's close capability. Simply tells the motor to move full speed in one direction, it is the commands responsibility to tell it when to stop closing. If the command doesn't, it will keep opening until the command ends and the default command ClawDoNothing takes over.

      • turnoff

        public void turnoff()
        Implements the claw's do nothing capability. Simply tells the motor to stop moving. After this is called the claw is neither opening or closing.
